-- South Africa's Current-Account Deficit to Widen `Gradually,' Minister Says
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2010-10-14T07:40:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/south-africa-s-current-account-deficit-to-widen-gradually-minister-says.html
South Africa’s current-account
deficit is expected to widen “gradually” over the next three
fiscal years as domestic demand and imports rise, Finance
Minister Pravin Gordhan said.  Weaker growth data since July points to slower expansion in
the second half, Gordhan said in a copy of a written
presentation to lawmakers in Cape Town today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
